data.current_description:
This endpoint gets called after the triggering the authorize flow.

Callback links need a state and code parameter to verify the validity of the request.
data.description_suggestion: Processes the OAuth authorization callback after a consumer completes authentication with a connector. This endpoint validates the authorization request using the state and code parameters to ensure security and prevent CSRF attacks. Upon successful validation, the connection is established and the consumer is redirected back to your application. Required parameters: state (for CSRF protection) and code (authorization code from the provider).
